        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>Nara (Japanese culture or style) [300018545], Early Historical Japanese [300106581], Japanese (culture or style) [300018519], East Asian [300018321], Asian [300018279], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the phase of the Nara period that developed from approximately 645 to 710. The style is represented by sculpture, primarily life-size bronze and smaller clay figures with slender lines, complicated drapery folds, and serene expressions.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refiere a la fase del período de Nara que se convirtió a otro estilo, cercanos a los años 645 a 710. El estilo es representado por la escultura, sobre todo bronce de tamaño natural y figuras más pequeñas de la arcilla con las líneas delgadas, dobleces complicados del drapeado, y expresiones serenas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de fase in de Nara-periode van circa 645 tot 710. De stijl komt tot uiting in de beeldhouwkunst, hoofdzakelijk in de vorm van levensgrote bronzen en kleinere kleifiguren met slanke lijnen, complex gevouwen draperieën en serene gezichtsuitdrukkingen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052390/Aarsbergen, Kroniek van de mensheid (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指西元645年至710年的奈良時代。雕刻是這時期的代表藝術，尤其是與實物大小相同以及體積較小的泥像雕，雕像的線條細長，有複雜的布料皺褶，臉部表情安詳。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
